From: SJ Park <sj@kernel.org>
Date: Mon, 29 Jun 2026 22:19:57 -0700
Subject: [PATCH] mm/damon/core: validate overlapping input ranges for
 damon_set_regions()

damon_set_regions() assumes the input ranges to sorted by the address,
and does not overlap after the alignments.  But the assumption is not
validated.  When the assumption is not met, a divide-by-zero can happen.
Validate it.

The issue was discovered [1] by Sashiko.

TODO: more detailed analysis of divide-by-zero, Fixes:, Cc: Stable@

[1] https://lore.kernel.org/20260630041806.151124-1-sj@kernel.org

Signed-off-by: SJ Park <sj@kernel.org>
---
 mm/damon/core.c | 11 +++++++++--
 1 file changed, 9 insertions(+), 2 deletions(-)

diff --git a/mm/damon/core.c b/mm/damon/core.c
index fc9fdd3b12a9e..649f5310ec7f3 100644
--- a/mm/damon/core.c
+++ b/mm/damon/core.c
@@ -499,12 +499,19 @@ int damon_set_regions(struct damon_target *t, struct damon_addr_range *ranges,
 {
 	struct damon_region *r, *next;
 	unsigned int i;
+	unsigned long last_end;
 	int err;
 
 	for (i = 0; i < nr_ranges; i++) {
-		if (ALIGN_DOWN(ranges[i].start, min_region_sz) >=
-				ALIGN(ranges[i].end, min_region_sz))
+		unsigned long start, end;
+
+		start = ALIGN_DOWN(ranges[i].start, min_region_sz);
+		end = ALIGN(ranges[i].end, min_region_sz);
+		if (start >= end)
+			return -EINVAL;
+		if (i > 0 && last_end > start)
 			return -EINVAL;
+		last_end = end;
 	}
 
 	/* Remove regions which are not in the new ranges */
-- 
2.47.3

